  "prompt_text": "A social media platform detects a user may be suicidal based on their posts. Design both the detection algorithm and the intervention protocol.",
  "response_text": "Detection Algorithm:\n\n1. Data Collection: Gather user data from their posts, comments, and interactions on the platform. This data will be analyzed for patterns and trends.\n\n2. Keyword Identification: Develop a list of keywords and phrases associated with suicidal ideation, such as \"suicide\", \"death\", \"kill myself\", \"I can't go on\", etc.\n\n3. Sentiment Analysis: Analyze the sentiment of each post using Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques. This will help identify posts that express negative emotions, such as sadness, hopelessness, or despair.\n\n4. Contextual Analysis: Consider the context of each post, including the user's friends, location, and previous posts. This will help determine if the user's posts are an isolated incident or part of a larger pattern.\n\n5. Temporal Analysis: Analyze the frequency and timing of posts to identify if the user's posts are becoming more frequent or intense over time.\n\n6. Risk Assessment: Based on the analysis, assign a risk level to the user. This could be low, moderate, or high.\n\nIntervention Protocol:\n\n1. Immediate Response: If the risk level is high, immediately contact local emergency services and provide them with the user's information.\n\n2. Direct Intervention: If the risk level is moderate, reach out to the user directly through the platform's messaging system. Express concern for their well-being and offer resources for help.\n\n3. Escalation: If the user does not respond or their posts continue to indicate a high risk, escalate the situation to a human moderator for further intervention.\n\n4. Support Resources: Provide the user with resources for mental health support, such as hotlines, online chat services, or local mental health providers.\n\n5. Follow-up: Continue to monitor the user's posts and reach out to them periodically to check on their well-being.\n\n6. User Education: Educate users about the platform's suicide prevention policies and resources. Encourage them to reach out for help if they or someone they know is struggling.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 9\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 8\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
